KATZ IS A NEW YORK-BORN-AND-BRED

18:00.079 --> 18:01.514
PAINTER WHO SPENDS HIS SUMMERS

18:01.514 --> 18:02.281
IN MAINE AND FINDS A LOT OF HIS

18:02.281 --> 18:03.749
INSPIRATION THERE.

18:03.749 --> 18:05.451
BEST KNOWN FOR HIS BRIGHT,

18:05.451 --> 18:07.320
BILLBOARD-SIZED PORTRAITS,

18:07.320 --> 18:08.821
KATZ'S WORK HAS BEEN THE SUBJECT

18:08.821 --> 18:09.522
OF TWO MUSEUM RETROSPECTIVES

18:09.522 --> 18:10.957
THIS YEAR.

18:10.957 --> 18:12.425
AND, AS THE NEWSHOUR'S PHIL

18:12.425 --> 18:13.159
HIRSCHKORN REPORTS, KATZ IS AS

18:13.159 --> 18:17.296
BUSY AS EVER.

18:17.296 --> 18:19.298
>> Reporter: EVEN AT 88-YEARS-

18:19.298 --> 18:20.599
OLD, ALEX KATZ PAINTS ALMOST

18:20.599 --> 18:22.301
EVERY DAY.

18:22.301 --> 18:25.204
>> I LIKE DOING IT.

18:25.204 --> 18:26.005
YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT'S GOING TO

18:26.005 --> 18:26.672
HAPPEN WHEN YOU START ON A

18:26.672 --> 18:27.106
CANVAS.

18:27.106 --> 18:28.507
I LOVE THE ADVENTURE.

18:28.507 --> 18:29.608
AND I LOVE STICKING IT TO PEOPLE

18:29.608 --> 18:30.409
WHO DIDN'T THINK I WAS ANYTHING

18:30.409 --> 18:32.845
FOR SO MANY YEARS.

18:32.845 --> 18:34.046
>> Reporter: STARTING OUT, KATZ

18:34.046 --> 18:35.314
THOUGHT HE COULD BE NEVER A

18:35.314 --> 18:36.015
FULL-TIME PAINTER WITHOUT A

18:36.015 --> 18:37.850
PART-TIME JOB.

18:37.850 --> 18:39.552
WHEN I SAT DOWN WITH HIM OUTSIDE

18:39.552 --> 18:40.987
HIS SUMMER STUDIO IN

18:40.987 --> 18:42.221
LINCONVILLE, MAINE, HE TOLD ME

18:42.221 --> 18:43.022
HIS FIRST GALLERY SHOWS DIDN'T

18:43.022 --> 18:45.091
SELL MUCH.

18:45.091 --> 18:48.527
>> I HAD FIVE FLOPS IN A ROW.

18:48.527 --> 18:49.328
>> Reporter: AND NOW, YOU'RE IN

18:49.328 --> 18:50.529
MUSEUMS ALL OVER THE WORLD.

18:50.529 --> 18:52.231
>> YEAH.

18:52.231 --> 18:53.466
I'M RIGHT NEAR THE TOP OF THE

18:53.466 --> 18:55.601
PYRAMID AT THIS POINT.

18:55.601 --> 18:56.869
>> Reporter: THIS SUMMER'S

18:56.869 --> 18:58.471
RETROSPECTIVE AT ATLANTA'S HIGH

